{"article_id":"Otb9subfWr32nAzl","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"U.S. officials on Tuesday challenged Russian President Vladimir Putin 's claim","depth":9},{"id":1,"text":"that Moscow 's hands are tied","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"when it comes to NSA leaker Edward Snowden ,","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"there is a `` clear legal basis ''","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"to turn him over .","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"Putin confirmed earlier Tuesday","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"that Snowden is at the Moscow airport .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"He said , though ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"that not only is Snowden in the transit zone ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"but","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"since Snowden has not committed a crime in Russia ,","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"the government will not extradite him back","depth":14},{"id":13,"text":"-- as requested --","depth":14},{"id":14,"text":"to the United States .","depth":13},{"id":15,"text":"Putin ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"speaking at a press conference in Finland ,","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"also said","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"he hopes","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"the Snowden case will not affect relations with the United States .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"He then dismissed U.S. accusations against Russia over the Snowden case as `` rubbish , ''","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"and added","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"that Russian security agencies `` did n't work","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"and are n't working '' with Snowden .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"Commenting on the U.S. request","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"to extradite him ,","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Putin said","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"Russia does n't have an extradition agreement with the U.S.","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"and thus would n't meet the U.S. request .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"Caitlin Hayden , a spokeswoman for the White House National Security Council , said","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"the absence of a treaty should not matter .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"`` While we do not have an extradition treaty with Russia ,","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"there is nonetheless a clear legal basis","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"to expel Mr. Snowden ,","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"based on the status of his travel documents and the pending charges against him , ''","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"`` Accordingly , we are asking the Russian Government to take action","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"to expel Mr. Snowden without delay","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"and to build upon the strong law enforcement cooperation","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"we have had , particularly since the Boston Marathon bombing . ''","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"U.S. Secretary of State John Kerry also acknowledged","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"there is no extradition treaty with Russia ,","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"but said","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"there are standards of behavior between nations .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Russia should not side with an international fugitive .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"`` There is respect for rule of law ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"and we would simply call on our friends in Russia to respect the fact","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"that a partner nation ... has made a normal request under legal systems","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"for law to be upheld , ''","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"Kerry said .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"`` We 're not looking for a confrontation .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"We 're not ordering anybody .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"We 're simply requesting , under a very normal procedure , for the transfer of somebody . ''","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"Other lawmakers urged the U.S. to be more forceful .","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"Sen. Lindsey Graham , R-S.C. , said","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"the U.S. should `` stand up to Putin . '' `` They 're defying us and the world ,","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"and I expect us to push back .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"I 've had it with this , ''","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"Graham said .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"Earlier Tuesday , Russia 's foreign minister Sergey Lavrov said","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"Snowden had n't even crossed into Russian territory","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"as he pushed back on U.S. demands .","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"`` We consider the attempts","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"to accuse Russia of violation of U.S. laws and even some sort of conspiracy ,","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"which on top of all that are accompanied by threats ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"as absolutely ungrounded and unacceptable , ''","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Lavrov said .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"`` There are no legal grounds for such conduct of U.S. officials ,","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"and we proceed from that . ''","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"The comments kicked off a full day of competing statements in the escalating stand-off between the two countries over the globetrotting fugitive .","depth":4},{"id":71,"text":"The leaker 's evasion of U.S. extradition efforts has added another headache for the Obama administration","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"as it grapples with the steady pace of intelligence leaks","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"that Snowden has set into motion .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"The administration is trying","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"-- strenuously ,","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"it appears --","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"to convince a string of countries","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"not known for their friendliness toward the U.S.","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"to keep Snowden in one place","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"while they negotiate his status .","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"Julian Assange , the WikiLeaks founder","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"whose team is assisting Snowden ,","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"said on Monday","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"that Snowden has applied for asylum in Ecuador , Iceland and possibly other countries .","depth":5},{"id":85,"text":"Meanwhile , Ecuador 's foreign minister said Monday","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"that the country was considering Snowden 's request .","depth":5},{"id":87,"text":"Graham on Monday also wrote a terse letter to Russian Ambassador Sergey Kislyak","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"that ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"if Snowden is still in Russia ,","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"Moscow should turn him over .","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"`` The Snowden case is an important test of the 'reset ' in relations between our two countries .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"Mr. Snowden 's own statements have made clear","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"his guilt .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"If our two nations are to have a constructive relationship","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"moving forward ,","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"Russian cooperation in this matter is essential , ''","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"he wrote .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"`` If Mr. Snowden is still on Russian territory ,","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"I urge your government to apprehend him","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"and turn him over to the United States authorities immediately . ''","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"Ecuador 's Foreign Minister Ricardo Patino spoke to reporters while in Vietnam on Monday ,","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"his country is analyzing Snowden 's request .","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"He was critical of the U.S. ,","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"it 's unlikely Snowden would receive a fair trial .","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"He said earlier","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"that the asylum request `` has to do with freedom of expression and with the security of citizens around the world . ''","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"Snowden helped The Guardian and The Washington Post disclose U.S. surveillance programs","depth":3},{"id":111,"text":"that collects vast amounts of phone records and online data in the name of foreign intelligence ,","depth":4},{"id":112,"text":"but often sweeping up information on American citizens .","depth":4},{"id":113,"text":"Officials have the ability","depth":4},{"id":114,"text":"to collect phone and Internet information broadly","depth":4},{"id":115,"text":"but need a warrant","depth":4},{"id":116,"text":"to examine specific cases","depth":5},{"id":117,"text":"where they believe","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"terrorism is involved .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":237,"left":228,"right":236,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":189,"right":227,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":189,"left":178,"right":188,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":172,"right":177,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":172,"left":142,"right":171,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":133,"right":141,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":124,"right":132,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":121,"right":123,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":121,"left":0,"right":120,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":3,"right":122,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":122,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":125,"right":131,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":125,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":131,"left":8,"right":130,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":130,"left":9,"right":129,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":129,"left":10,"right":128,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":128,"lef